Subject: [PATCH 1521/2588] drm/i915: Don't mask the return code whilst
 relocating.

The return from move_to_gtt_domain() may indicate a pending signal which
needs to handled as opposed to an actual error, for instance, so report
the original return value rather than forcing an EINVAL.

Signed-off-by: Chris Wilson <chris@chris-wilson.co.uk>
(cherry picked from commit 1cdf7fef793c715d8c4998575aba3741fa4a0b01)

Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem.c
index 822defb..e3b8ea4 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/i915_gem.c
@@ -3457,7 +3457,7 @@ i915_gem_object_pin_and_relocate(struct drm_gem_object *obj,
 		if (ret != 0) {
 			drm_gem_object_unreference(target_obj);
 			i915_gem_object_unpin(obj);
-			return -EINVAL;
+			return ret;
 		}
 
